      <description>&lt;p&gt;Technical analysis of mining behavior exhibited by an entity that is plausibly Satoshi Nakamoto.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#34;book-hint btc&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p&gt;This article by &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/lopp&#34;&gt;Jameson Lopp&lt;/a&gt; was published in his &lt;a href=&#34;https://blog.lopp.net/was-satoshi-a-greedy-miner&#34;&gt;blog&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/contribute/&#34;&gt;Contribute&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If you spend enough time in the crypto ecosystem then you&amp;rsquo;ll no doubt come across arguments that some projects have unfair token distributions because they were &amp;ldquo;premined&amp;rdquo; / &amp;ldquo;instamined&amp;rdquo; / &amp;ldquo;fast mined&amp;rdquo; by the project founders, effectively enriching themselves from the initial launch of the project.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
